==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Justifier
<hw>Jus"ti*fi`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who
justifies; one who vindicates, supports, defends, or absolves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Justifiers</qex> of themselves and hypocrites.</q>
<rj><qau>Strype.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That he might be just, and the <qex>justifier</qex> of him which
believeth in Jesus.</q> <rj><qau>Rom. iii. 26.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Justify</ent>⟦br⟧
